(NULL,'Delhivery','69474','Anindya','Bhoomit Ahlawat','The automation "10. Reverse Integration - New Lead - Clone" at Delhivery''s tenant is encountering recurring daily failures at the CallLapp24 action node, between 12 AM – 2 AM IST. The failure is returning HTTP 429 (Too Many Requests) on the Lapp invocation, as captured in the auto-generated failure notification stack trace (MX.Radon.Workflow.Business.BusinessProcess.Actions.CallLapp.ExecuteAsync → RestHelper.Post). The 429 indicates a rate-limit breach — either on the Lapp execution throttle (internal) or on the downstream API the Lapp is invoking (external). The deterministic time window (12-2 AM) suggests a scheduled batch / high-volume lead ingestion at the customer''s end during off-peak hours, triggering automation fires above the permissible rate limit. Failures result in Reverse Integration lead clones being skipped for the affected leads, impacting downstream routing and reporting. Confirm the source of the 429 — internal Lapp/automation throttle vs. external third-party API. Pull automation execution logs for the past 7 days within the 12-2 AM window — total fires, failure rate, retry behavior. Identify the trigger pattern causing the spike during this window (scheduled batch / bulk push at customer''s end). Share RCA and recommended mitigation — throttle adjustment / retry logic / customer-side load staggering.','P1','Mohith Raj Cm',1896512,NULL,'Integration Failures','LAPP/UDS/Batch Job issues','2026-05-11',NULL,'Open','Tech Support team to Identify the target endpoint invoked by CallLapp24 (Lapp URL + downstream API).'),
(NULL,'Urbanrise','52908','Anindya','Bhoomit Ahlawat','Lead Field Audit Report (System Report): Phone Number and Lead Number missing; report shows only Lead ID (prospect ID) which is not searchable; no hyperlink to open the lead. Customer search keys (phone/lead number) absent, report unusable for management. System report - editable only by Engineering from back-end.','P1','Reports / Engineering',NULL,NULL,'Reports & Dashboards','Reports & Dashboards related','2026-05-30',NULL,'In Progress','Step 1: CSM to log Product Support ticket routed to L4/Engineering for back-end fix (Aditya Swaroop). Step 2: CSM+PS review with customer Mon 3 PM to evaluate custom Sierra report.'),
(NULL,'Urbanrise','76483','Anindya','Bhoomit Ahlawat','Lead Ownership Audit Report (System Report): shows old owner and new owner correctly, but date column labelled "Created Date" while the relevant change date is Modified On; Created Date / Prospect Created Date / Modified On are three confusing terms for end users. Earlier (Logi) it was simply Activity Date. System report - editable only by Engineering from back-end.','P1','Reports / Engineering',NULL,NULL,'Configuration Failures','UI/UX friction','2026-05-30',NULL,'In Progress','Updated report shared with customer for go-ahead (Tenant 76483); on confirmation replicate across all tenants. Back-end label change needs Engineering.'),
