(NULL,'UpGrad','79025','Anindya','Abhishek Reddy','RE: [#154624] TECHIORA LABS PRIVATE LIMITED || Data Push Not working','P1','Support',154624,NULL,'Integration Failures','Data sync issues',NULL,'18-04-2026','Resolved','Mcube mentioned they had some issue where there was a delay in pushing the Call Logs to us, and that it was fixed.'),
(NULL,'TopRankers','53052','Anindya','Abhishek Reddy','RE: [#1884992] Error in automation','P2','Support',1884992,NULL,'Integration Failures','Data sync issues',NULL,'29/04/2026','Resolved','Cx raised query on why an automation has moved down a certain path instead of the expected. Support team to review and confirm.  29-Apr - related to Audit trail issue. Fix was released on 16 April. Older data will not be visible in audit trail'),
(NULL,'Rank Guru','54664','Anindya','Abhishek Reddy','RE: [#1883314] RE: Request to Enable Sales Group Hierarchy for Accurate Demo Counts','P2','Support',1883314,NULL,'PS','Feature Request',NULL,'20-04-2026','Resolved','20-Apr - Support team explained that If the logged-in sales user is a manager of any sales group within the tenant, all users in that group will be visible in the report. You can verify this by checking the Sales Group filter values. If the sales user is only a member of a sales group, they will be able to see only their own data, and the Sales Group filter will appear empty.'),
(NULL,'Flobiz','63074','Anindya','Abhishek Reddy','RE: [#8684] Urgent: Freshdesk Tickets Showing Open in Marvin – 85K Cases','P1','Support',8684,NULL,'PS','Adoption / Stickiness Risk',NULL,'20/04/2026','Resolved','There were around 45k tickets that got re-created in Open Status, as the customer had made some changes on their end. 20-Apr - To solve this, we have suggested deleting those tickets, so as to avoid duplicate tickets.'),
(NULL,'Flobiz','63074','Anindya','Abhishek Reddy','RE: [#1885415] RE: Blank Line in Bot Interaction report - 63074','P2','Product',1885415,NULL,'Reports & Dashboards','Reports & Dashboards related',NULL,'20-04-2026','Resolved','The Bot Interaction report had certain blank lines and mismatched information related to Chat handover to agent. Issue was raised to product team to resolve. 20-Apr - CSM confirmed that the report seems to be working fine. Informed customer. Awaiting confirmation from cx.'),
(NULL,'Rank Guru','54664','Anindya','Abhishek Reddy','RE: [#1883718] Delay in Outbound Call Activity Sync on LSQ','P1','Support',1883718,NULL,'Integration Failures','Data sync issues',NULL,'20-04-2026','Resolved','Cx raised issue informing that the Call Log activities were not synching in real-time. They were being displayed on activity history with lot of delay. 20-Apr - Support confirmed that this is due to async API usage, which does not have any defined SLA. There was ertain delays observed during 16-17 Apr.'),
(NULL,'Rank Guru','72070','Anindya','Nikhil Chand','Re: [#1885487] Issue with Outbound Call Talk Time Not Capturing in LSQ & Support Required for Report Creation','P1','Support',1885487,NULL,'Integration Failures','Data sync issues',NULL,'14/05/2026','Resolved','Customer raised ticket informing that the outbound call activities are not being posted as expected, especially the activity or the recording is not available. 20-Apr - Support team checked the samples and informed that the vendor was not pushing the details. Vendor team to check and get back.'),
(NULL,'TopRankers','53052','Anindya','Abhishek Reddy','“Whatsapp Input Requirement” field not getting updated','P2','Support',1885585,NULL,'Configuration Failures','Configuration errors',NULL,'30/04/2026','Resolved','Cx complained that the Whatsapp Input Requirement data lead field was not updated. This usually gets updated when lead selects the exam they are targeting! 30-Apr - Support shared RCA that the chatbot flow needed to be changed to get the required value into the field.'),
(NULL,'TopRankers','53052','Anindya','Abhishek Reddy','RE: [#1884619] Automation Not working properly','P1','Support',1884619,NULL,'Integration Failures','Data sync issues',NULL,'25/04/2026','Resolved','Leads are being assigned as system and not following logic in automation.  Possible RCA: Sync issue that prevented updated data from being saved Corrective Action:  The card IfElse72 was re saved via Live Edit, and the changes are now reflected in the Automation DB.'),
(NULL,'Cordlife','67219','Anindya',NULL,'In the report (Report Name: Vendor Visit Report SIERA- March 24) In the drilldown section - we need to add the Lead Name as a data parameters (Lead Field) - schema name - FirstName 2. In the report (Report Name : Opportunity Deleted Report ) Need to add Banking_Opportunity_UniqueID1 (opportunity field) - schema name - ProspectActivityAutoId','P1','Product',NULL,NULL,'Reports & Dashboards','Reports & Dashboards related','2026-04-20',NULL,'In Progress',NULL),
